    },
    {
      "id": "detailed_4_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "detailed_4",
      "description": "This vehicle is being sold in fair condition, and the asking price reflects that honestly \u2014 please read this full description before reaching out. The car is drivable and functional for everyday use, but it comes with noticeable wear and imperfections that you should be aware of before purchasing. Expect some cosmetic blemishes such as scratches, scuffs, or minor dents on the exterior, and the interior shows signs of regular use including worn upholstery and surface wear on high-touch areas. Mechanically, the car runs and drives, but it may have some minor issues or deferred maintenance items that a new owner should plan to address \u2014 nothing that prevents daily driving, but worth factoring into your budget. It has not been freshly detailed or reconditioned, so what you see is what you get. This is a solid choice for a buyer who needs reliable transportation and doesn't mind putting a little work or money into bringing it up further. All known issues have been disclosed to the best of my ability, and I encourage a pre-purchase inspection by a trusted mechanic before committing.",
      "price": 15500.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "fair",
      "quality_value": 0.4,
      "timestep_posted": 22
    },
    {
      "id": "detailed_3_listing_0",
      "firm_id": "detailed_3",
      "description": "We're listing this vehicle honestly as a car in good condition, and we want any potential buyer to have a clear, accurate picture before reaching out. The exterior presents well overall \u2014 the paint retains a decent shine with only minor blemishes, small scratches, or light swirl marks consistent with normal everyday use. There are no major dents or rust concerns, though a close inspection will reveal the typical wear you'd expect from a used vehicle that has been driven regularly. The interior is clean and functional, with seating that shows moderate use \u2014 think light wear on high-contact areas like the driver's seat and steering wheel, but nothing that would be considered damage. All primary controls, electronics, and comfort features are in working order. Mechanically, the car runs reliably and has been maintained, though it is not without the minor imperfections that come with age and mileage. Buyers should expect a solid, dependable vehicle that is ready for daily driving, but not a showroom-fresh experience. We encourage an in-person inspection and welcome any questions \u2014 we believe in transparency and want you to feel confident in your purchase.",
